CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 22, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Reprimanded - Sore at the guilty verdict in Beaver County discrimination case, Mrs. Betty Jean Wilson, who had refused service at a night club to Negroes, delivered some sharp remarks to three jury members and received a strong reprimand and a $50 fine from Judge Robert E. McCreary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women, including Betty Jean Wilson, standing center surrounded by three men, gathered in government office during discrimination trial, Beaver County
